name: HKElectrocardiogram.Classification
desc: Classifications returned by Apple Watch’s ECG algorithm.

items.name: case sinusRhythm
items.desc: The sample exhibits no signs of atrial fibrillation.

items.name: case atrialFibrillation
items.desc: The sample exhibits signs of atrial fibrillation.

items.name: case inconclusiveHighHeartRate
items.desc: An unclassifiable sample caused by a rapid heart rate.

items.name: case inconclusiveLowHeartRate
items.desc: An unclassifiable sample caused by a heart rate below 50 bpm.

items.name: case inconclusivePoorReading
items.desc: An unclassifiable sample caused by an unclear signal.

items.name: case inconclusiveOther
items.desc: An unclassifiable sample caused by an unknown issue.

items.name: case unrecognized
items.desc: A sample classification that this version of HealthKit doesn’t recognize.

items.name: case notSet
items.desc: A sample that doesn’t have an assigned classification.
